    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-24T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="740"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.7131/88</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Rumanian Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Nano</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-24">February 24,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 686/P–26</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your note No. 611.7131/74 of
                    December 13, 1929,<note n="6" xml:id="d740fn6">Not printed.</note> I have the
                    honour to inform you that my Government would like the agreement according
                    mutual unconditional most-favored-nation treatment in customs matters, which was
                    signed February 26, 1926,<note n="7" xml:id="d740fn7">
                        <ref target="frus1926v02#pg_898">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1926, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">ii</hi>, p. 898</ref>.</note> to remain in force
                    until May 1 instead of March 1.</p>
                <pb facs="0885" n="791" xml:id="pg_791"/>
                <p>My Government wishes to know whether this is agreeable to the Government of the
                    United States, and would be grateful if their decision could be communicated to
                    this Legation as soon as feasible.</p>
                <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">F. C. Nano</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
